#- §lSpecial Foreign News Section

§0§nCascadia and Columbia at war:
§0After a supposed incursion on Nyasaland territory by Cascadian forces, Columbia officially declared war on Cascadia, saying that they were protecting their allies. The War 
#- seems to be fueled by the rivalry between the two nations.
The Cascadian skybunker has already been entered and looted by Columbian forces, however, no official declaration concerning the end of the war  has been made, leaving the international
#- community in suspense.

§0§nDormount moves away from democracy:
§0The young Republic of Dormount is a republic no more, the nation has moved on to being a dictatorship. Dictator PoweringMC has not denied this, and in fact is not hiding it all. It was revealed that he has
#- said on an internal DUMP discord channel that “Dormount is being converted into a dictatorship.” When asked, he has stated that “democracy doesn't work for a small nation” but that he will “work for the prosperity of [his] people”.  Whether he makes true on these promises remains to
#- be seen.
Regardless, the light of a young democracy being extinguished is always a sad thing. It seems most nations in Civ Classic are simple authoritarian governments, with no respect for the common people; hopefully this can change in the future.
#- §0§nEM Newfriends Quit:
§0Oko, de-facto leader of Eddie Murphy, has said that the bulk of EM Newfriends quit due to the outcome of the Cascadian-Columbian war, with Columbia having supposedly destroyed all of EM’s XP Infrastructure. Whether the EM-Pire recoups from this
#- event or whether it becomes an inactive nation remains to be seen, we hope for the best.
§7
Paper written and edited by DetectiveAmandaCC. You can get the paper in game at the Rock Paper Scissors store in the Mount September Mall.
